{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_52","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"source .venv/bin/activate && python - << 'PY'\nimport json, re, pathlib\nmeta=json.load(open('/tmp/paper_meta.json'))\nreasons={\n'2310.15213':'Directly studies function vectors, including semantic vector composition in residual activations.',\n'2312.06681':'Core residual-stream steering method (CAA) with clear vector construction and evaluation.',\n'2308.10248':'Foundational activation engineering paper introducing ActAdd steering.',\n'2410.12877':'Instruction-specific steering vectors and explicit multi-instruction composition experiments.',\n'2506.03292':'Scalable hypernetwork-based steering vector generation baseline for large steering sets.',\n'2602.01654':'Context-dependent steering vector fields; highlights limits of static global linear directions.',\n'2602.02385':'Tests whether residual representations factor into orthogonal subspaces; central to compositionality hypothesis.',\n'2301.05217':'Mechanistic interpretability methodology and metrics useful for tracking emergent internal structure.',\n'2406.17563':'Dynamic composition of multiple steering properties with information-theoretic weighting.'\n}\n# map ids to filenames\nfiles={p.name.split('_')[0]:p.name for p in pathlib.Path('papers').glob('*.pdf')}\nlines=['# Downloaded Papers','']\nfor i,p in enumerate(meta,1):\n    fn=files[p['id']]\n    lines.append(f\\\"{i}. [{p['title']}]({fn})\\\")\n    lines.append(f\\\"   - Authors: {', '.join(a.replace(',', '') for a in p['authors'][:8])}{' et al.' if len(p['authors'])>8 else ''}\\\")\n    lines.append(f\\\"   - Year: {p['year']}\\\")\n    lines.append(f\\\"   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/{p['id']}\\\")\n    lines.append(f\\\"   - Why relevant: {reasons.get(p['id'],'Relevant to residual-stream directionality and steering.')}\\\")\n    lines.append('')\nopen('papers/README.md','w').write('\\\\n'.join(lines))\nprint('wrote papers/README.md')\nPY\nsed -n '1,220p' papers/README.md\"","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_52","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"source .venv/bin/activate && python - << 'PY'\nimport json, re, pathlib\nmeta=json.load(open('/tmp/paper_meta.json'))\nreasons={\n'2310.15213':'Directly studies function vectors, including semantic vector composition in residual activations.',\n'2312.06681':'Core residual-stream steering method (CAA) with clear vector construction and evaluation.',\n'2308.10248':'Foundational activation engineering paper introducing ActAdd steering.',\n'2410.12877':'Instruction-specific steering vectors and explicit multi-instruction composition experiments.',\n'2506.03292':'Scalable hypernetwork-based steering vector generation baseline for large steering sets.',\n'2602.01654':'Context-dependent steering vector fields; highlights limits of static global linear directions.',\n'2602.02385':'Tests whether residual representations factor into orthogonal subspaces; central to compositionality hypothesis.',\n'2301.05217':'Mechanistic interpretability methodology and metrics useful for tracking emergent internal structure.',\n'2406.17563':'Dynamic composition of multiple steering properties with information-theoretic weighting.'\n}\n# map ids to filenames\nfiles={p.name.split('_')[0]:p.name for p in pathlib.Path('papers').glob('*.pdf')}\nlines=['# Downloaded Papers','']\nfor i,p in enumerate(meta,1):\n    fn=files[p['id']]\n    lines.append(f\\\"{i}. [{p['title']}]({fn})\\\")\n    lines.append(f\\\"   - Authors: {', '.join(a.replace(',', '') for a in p['authors'][:8])}{' et al.' if len(p['authors'])>8 else ''}\\\")\n    lines.append(f\\\"   - Year: {p['year']}\\\")\n    lines.append(f\\\"   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/{p['id']}\\\")\n    lines.append(f\\\"   - Why relevant: {reasons.get(p['id'],'Relevant to residual-stream directionality and steering.')}\\\")\n    lines.append('')\nopen('papers/README.md','w').write('\\\\n'.join(lines))\nprint('wrote papers/README.md')\nPY\nsed -n '1,220p' papers/README.md\"","aggregated_output":"wrote papers/README.md\n# Downloaded Papers\n\n1. [Function Vectors in Large Language Models](2310.15213_function_vectors_in_large_language_models.pdf)\n   - Authors: Todd Eric, Li Millicent L., Sharma Arnab Sen, Mueller Aaron, Wallace Byron C., Bau David\n   - Year: 2023\n   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.15213\n   - Why relevant: Directly studies function vectors, including semantic vector composition in residual activations.\n\n2. [Steering Llama 2 via Contrastive Activation Addition](2312.06681_steering_llama_2_via_contrastive_activation_addition.pdf)\n   - Authors: Panickssery Nina, Gabrieli Nick, Schulz Julian, Tong Meg, Hubinger Evan, Turner Alexander Matt\n   - Year: 2023\n   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2312.06681\n   - Why relevant: Core residual-stream steering method (CAA) with clear vector construction and evaluation.\n\n3. [Steering Language Models With Activation Engineering](2308.10248_steering_language_models_with_activation_engineering.pdf)\n   - Authors: Turner Alexander Matt, Thiergart Lisa, Leech Gavin, Udell David, Vazquez Juan J., Mini Ulisse, MacDiarmid Monte\n   - Year: 2023\n   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2308.10248\n   - Why relevant: Foundational activation engineering paper introducing ActAdd steering.\n\n4. [Improving Instruction-Following in Language Models through Activation Steering](2410.12877_improving_instruction_following_in_language_models_through_a.pdf)\n   - Authors: Stolfo Alessandro, Balachandran Vidhisha, Yousefi Safoora, Horvitz Eric, Nushi Besmira\n   - Year: 2024\n   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.12877\n   - Why relevant: Instruction-specific steering vectors and explicit multi-instruction composition experiments.\n\n5. [HyperSteer: Activation Steering at Scale with Hypernetworks](2506.03292_hypersteer_activation_steering_at_scale_with_hypernetworks.pdf)\n   - Authors: Sun Jiuding, Baskaran Sidharth, Wu Zhengxuan, Sklar Michael, Potts Christopher, Geiger Atticus\n   - Year: 2025\n   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.03292\n   - Why relevant: Scalable hypernetwork-based steering vector generation baseline for large steering sets.\n\n6. [Steering Vector Fields for Context-Aware Inference-Time Control in Large Language Models](2602.01654_steering_vector_fields_for_context_aware_inference_time_cont.pdf)\n   - Authors: Li Jiaqian, Li Yanshu, Huang Kuan-Hao\n   - Year: 2026\n   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.01654\n   - Why relevant: Context-dependent steering vector fields; highlights limits of static global linear directions.\n\n7. [Transformers learn factored representations](2602.02385_transformers_learn_factored_representations.pdf)\n   - Authors: Shai Adam, Amdahl-Culleton Loren, Christensen Casper L., Bigelow Henry R., Rosas Fernando E., Boyd Alexander B., Alt Eric A., Ray Kyle J. et al.\n   - Year: 2026\n   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.02385\n   - Why relevant: Tests whether residual representations factor into orthogonal subspaces; central to compositionality hypothesis.\n\n8. [Progress measures for grokking via mechanistic interpretability](2301.05217_progress_measures_for_grokking_via_mechanistic_interpretabil.pdf)\n   - Authors: Nanda Neel, Chan Lawrence, Lieberum Tom, Smith Jess, Steinhardt Jacob\n   - Year: 2023\n   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2301.05217\n   - Why relevant: Mechanistic interpretability methodology and metrics useful for tracking emergent internal structure.\n\n9. [Multi-property Steering of Large Language Models with Dynamic Activation Composition](2406.17563_multi_property_steering_of_large_language_models_with_dynami.pdf)\n   - Authors: Scalena Daniel, Sarti Gabriele, Nissim Malvina\n   - Year: 2024\n   - arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2406.17563\n   - Why relevant: Dynamic composition of multiple steering properties with information-theoretic weighting.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_53","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > datasets/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Datasets\n\nThis directory contains datasets for studying compositionality of linear directions and activation steering in LLM residual streams. Data files are not intended for git commits; see \"'`.gitignore`.\n\n## Dataset 1: TruthfulQA (multiple-choice validation)\n\n### Overview\n- Source: `truthful_qa` (Hugging Face datasets)\n- Size: 817 examples\n- Format: Hugging Face Dataset saved to disk\n- Task: Truthfulness / misconception resistance (MCQA)\n- Splits: validation\n- License: Check dataset card on Hugging Face\n\n### Download Instructions\n\nUsing Hugging Face (recommended):\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\n\nds = load_dataset(\"truthful_qa\", \"multiple_choice\", split=\"validation\")\nds.save_to_disk(\"datasets/truthful_qa_multiple_choice_validation\")\n```\n\n### Loading the Dataset\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_from_disk\n\nds = load_from_disk(\"datasets/truthful_qa_multiple_choice_validation\")\nprint(len(ds), ds.column_names)\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- Saved sample: `datasets/truthful_qa_multiple_choice_validation/samples/samples.json`\n\n### Notes\n- Useful for testing whether truthfulness-related steering vectors transfer across prompts.\n- Can be used for evaluating direction consistency and side effects.\n\n## Dataset 2: IFEval (train)\n\n### Overview\n- Source: `google/IFEval` (Hugging Face datasets)\n- Size: 541 examples\n- Format: Hugging Face Dataset saved to disk\n- Task: Instruction-following constraints (format/length/keywords)\n- Splits: train\n- License: Check dataset card on Hugging Face\n\n### Download Instructions\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\n\nds = load_dataset(\"google/IFEval\", split=\"train\")\nds.save_to_disk(\"datasets/google_ifeval_train\")\n```\n\n### Loading the Dataset\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_from_disk\n\nds = load_from_disk(\"datasets/google_ifeval_train\")\nprint(len(ds), ds.column_names)\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- Saved sample: `datasets/google_ifeval_train/samples/samples.json`\n\n### Notes\n- Strong fit for multi-property composition experiments.\n- Supports evaluating whether summed directions satisfy multiple constraints simultaneously.\n\n## Dataset 3: HellaSwag (validation)\n\n### Overview\n- Source: `Rowan/hellaswag` (Hugging Face datasets)\n- Size: 10,042 examples\n- Format: Hugging Face Dataset saved to disk\n- Task: Commonsense completion / robustness check\n- Splits: validation\n- License: Check dataset card on Hugging Face\n\n### Download Instructions\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\n\nds = load_dataset(\"Rowan/hellaswag\", split=\"validation\")\nds.save_to_disk(\"datasets/rowan_hellaswag_validation\")\n```\n\n### Loading the Dataset\n```python\nfrom datasets import load_from_disk\n\nds = load_from_disk(\"datasets/rowan_hellaswag_validation\")\nprint(len(ds), ds.column_names)\n```\n\n### Sample Data\n- Saved sample: `datasets/rowan_hellaswag_validation/samples/samples.json`\n\n### Notes\n- Useful as an off-target capability retention benchmark after steering.\n- Helps detect regressions when applying steering vectors.\n\n## Validation Summary\n\nQuick checks performed:\n- Loaded each saved dataset from disk successfully.\n- Verified row counts and schema.\n- Saved first 10 records for each dataset in `samples/samples.json`.\n\nMachine-readable summary: `datasets/dataset_summary.json`\nEOF\n\nsed -n '\"'1,260p' datasets/README.md\"","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
